top 10 programming languages on github + pull requests and issues

# clear workspace for new project
rm(list = ls())

# importing libraries
library(ggplot2)
## Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 4.0.5
# retreiving colors from R excluding gray colors
colors <- grDevices::colors()[grep('gr(a|e)y', grDevices::colors(), invert = T)]
# importing datasets
repos <- read.csv('repos.csv')
issues <- read.csv('issues.csv')
prs <- read.csv('prs.csv')

analysing repos dataset

# sort repos in descending order
repos <- repos[order(-repos$num_repos), ]

# take top 10 rows
repos <- repos[1:10,]

# take the languages from repos to be used on other dataset
languages <- repos$language
repos
languages
##  [1] "JavaScript" "CSS"        "HTML"       "Shell"      "Python"    
##  [6] "Ruby"       "Java"       "PHP"        "C"          "C++"

analyzing issues and prs datasets

# extract unique years from issues and prs datasets 
years_prs <- unique(prs$year)
years_issues <- unique(issues$year)

# make sure that years on issues and prs are the same
years_issues == years_prs
##  [1] TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE
years <- unique(issues$year)

years
##  [1] 2011 2012 2013 2014 2015 2016 2017 2018 2019 2020 2021 2022
# create an empty dataframe 
issues_prs <- data.frame(
  languages = character(),
  years = integer(), 
  issues = integer(),
  prs = integer(),
  stringsAsFactors = FALSE
)
# loop through languages and years vectors and filter matching values
for(language in languages){
  for (year in years){
    total_issues <- sum(issues[issues$year == year & issues$name == language, c('count')])
    total_prs <- sum(prs[prs$year == year & prs$name == language, c('count')])
    # append matching values to the created dataset
    issues_prs[nrow(issues_prs) + 1,] <- c(language, year, total_issues, total_prs)
  }
}

visualization

# visualizing repos
ggplot() + 
  geom_bar(
    aes(
      x = repos$language,
      y = repos$num_repos
    ),
    stat = 'identity',
    # get n random colors using the length of languages vector 
    fill = sample(colors, length(languages)),
    color = 'black'
    
  ) + 
  ggtitle('Top 10 Programming Languages on Github') +
  xlab('Language') + 
  ylab('Number of Repositories') +
  theme_light()

# visualizing issues and prs by year
for (year in years) {
  yearly_data <-
    issues_prs[issues_prs$year == year, c('languages', 'issues', 'prs')]
  title <- paste0('Number of Issues and Pull Requests of ' , year)
  plot <- ggplot() +
    geom_bar(
      aes(x = yearly_data$language,
          y = yearly_data$issues),
      stat = 'identity',
      # get n random colors using the length of languages vector
      fill = 'steelblue',
      color = 'black'
    ) +
    geom_bar(
      aes(x = yearly_data$language,
          y = yearly_data$prs),
      stat = 'identity',
      # get n random colors using the length of languages vector
      fill = 'springgreen',
      color = 'black'
    ) +
    ggtitle(title) +
    xlab('Language') +
    ylab('Number of Issues and Pull Requests') +
    theme_light()
  print(plot)
}

summarizing total number of issues and pull requests to a time series data

# create new empty dataframe
total_issues_prs <- data.frame(year = integer(),
                               issues = integer(),
                               prs = integer())

for (year in years){
 total_issues <-  sum(issues[issues$year == year, c('count')])
 total_prs <-  sum(prs[prs$year == year, c('count')])
 total_issues_prs[nrow(total_issues_prs) + 1,] <-
   c( year, total_issues, total_prs)
}

visualizing total issues and prs

ggplot() +
  geom_line(
    aes(x = total_issues_prs$year,
        y = total_issues_prs$issues),
    color = 'steelblue'
  ) +
  geom_point(
    aes(x = total_issues_prs$year,
        y = total_issues_prs$issues),
    color = 'steelblue'
  ) +
  geom_line(
    aes(x = total_issues_prs$year,
        y = total_issues_prs$prs),
    color = 'springgreen'
  ) +
  geom_point(
    aes(x = total_issues_prs$year,
        y = total_issues_prs$prs),
    color = 'springgreen'
  ) +
  ggtitle('Total Number of Issues from year (2011 - 2022)') +
  xlab('Language') +
  ylab('Number of Issues and Prs') +
  theme_light()
